## Command: status

Check in-flight agents, update state, report progress.

1. Read state file
2. Check in-session tasks via TaskList:
   - Completed → update state to `done`
   - Still running → report as in-progress
   - Missing (session restart) → check for branch in repo (`git branch -r`); if found with commits → `done-needs-review`, else → `blocked` ("agent session lost")
3. Check for PRs on branches without a PR recorded
4. Write updated state file
5. Report: in-progress, completed, blocked, needs-human-attention

---

## Safety Rules
- NEVER modify, checkout, or force-push to any branch not prefixed with `{{ .ado.branchPrefix }}`
- NEVER run destructive git commands (reset --hard, clean -f, etc.) outside of worktrees
- ALWAYS use isolated worktrees (via Agent tool with isolation: "worktree") for implementation
- Branch naming: `{{ .ado.branchPrefix }}<workitem-id>-<short-description>`
- Only open DRAFT PRs — never publish or merge
- Never modify the user's current working tree or checked-out branch
- State file (~/cockpit/state/ado-tasks.md) is the ONLY mutable file the cockpit session writes to (besides agent worktrees)
